{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Four-fold serial dilutions (1:4 to 1:16,384) of macaque serum samples were prepared in 96-well plates using DMEM supplemented with 5% fetal bovine serum (FBS).",
    "Then, 40 μL of each dilution was transferred to a separate 96-well plate, mixed with an equal volume of AAV9:CAG-GFP-P2A-Luciferase-WPRE-SV40 vector (4-8 × 10 7 vg per 40 μL, diluted in DMEM-5% FBS), and incubated for 1 h at 37 °C.",
    "Following the incubation, AAV-serum samples were transferred into a new 96-well plate (20 μL triplicates) and a total of 80 μL of DMEM-5% fetal bovine serum, containing 20,000 HEK293T cells, was added to each well (final volume of 100 μL).",
    "96-well plates were incubated for 48 h at 37 °C, 5% CO 2.",
    "Luminescence levels were read using a Perkin-Elmer Victor Luminescence Plate Reader using the britelite plus Reporter Gene Assay System (Perkin-Elmer, #6066761)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}